  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`: v1.9.20-stable-979fc968\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX: Debian 4.19.0-10-amd64 / Docker 18.09.1\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nNode runs without null pointers\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nNode crashes due to a null pointer exception\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Start docker container with following `docker-compose.yml`\r\n```\r\nversion: \"3\"\r\n\r\nservices:\r\n  geth:\r\n    image: ethereum/client-go:v1.9.20\r\n    restart: unless-stopped\r\n    command: \"--syncmode light --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0\"\r\n    volumes:\r\n      - \"./data:/root\"\r\n```\r\n2. Wait about 3 hours until error occurs\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\ngeth_1  | INFO [09-02|11:45:51.541] Imported new block headers               count=192  elapsed=259.163ms number=10779558 hash=\"1c0744â€¦7e0293\" age=7h41m13s\r\ngeth_1  | panic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\ngeth_1  | [signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x1c0 pc=0xd25a18]\r\ngeth_1  | \r\ngeth_1  | goroutine 93 [running]:\r\ngeth_1  | github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).reorgOnNewHead(0xc0003cb4a0, 0x149f340, 0xc00288cc60, 0xc0014c7440, 0xc00288cc60, 0xc0015accc0, 0x46b52c)\r\ngeth_1  | \tgithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:229 +0x238\r\ngeth_1  | github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).setNewHead(0xc0003cb4a0, 0xc0014c7440)\r\ngeth_1  | \tgithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:310 +0xf7\r\ngeth_1  | github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.(*TxPool).eventLoop(0xc0003cb4a0)\r\ngeth_1  | \tgithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:291 +0x56\r\ngeth_1  | created by github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light.NewTxPool\r\ngeth_1  | \tgithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/light/txpool.go:108 +0x3da\r\n````\r\n",
